		<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName> <date>July 6&#44; 1851</date>.</p>
		<p><addressee>Rev Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">Dear Sir&#44;</p>
          <p rend="indent(3)">In haste I take<lb/> my pen to inform you that <persName>Mr. H. L. Moss</persName><lb/> at <placeName>Dayton Ohio</placeName> wishes to be a subscriber for your<lb/> Occident commencing with the <date>June</date> No. of this<lb/> year. Please send it to him.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">I do not yet know whether I can get subscribers<lb/> enough to sustain the Shulamite&#44; but if I do&#44; it may<lb/> be commenced soon. If you have time to drop me a<lb/> few lines&#44; I wish you would give me your opinion<lb/> on the subject and whether you think it will meet<lb/> with favor in your region. If it go on it will cer&#61;<lb/>tainly be what it proposes to be&#8212;a paper open to Jews<lb/> as well as Christians&#8212;a paper in which Judaism may<lb/> be defended and advanced&#44; though it will circulate<lb/> much more among Christians&#44; than Jews&#8212;probably five times<lb/> as much. I would be glad to have your <hi rend="underline">private</hi> opinion.<lb/> I do not wish any public notice. Address me <placeName>95 Greene Street</placeName>.</p>
          <p rend="indent(7)">Yours most respectfully</p>
          <p rend="indent(8)"><persName role="author">M. R. Miller</persName></p>
          
        </body>
    </text>
